  <span id="freeText16367485461910543298" style="display:none">I really enjoyed this story of Mildred Pierce's life as a young mother and wife in the 1930's, and how she survives divorce, personal heartbreak and drama, and goes on to build her huge, successful restaurant business.....<br /><br />Well, that's not the whole story, of course -- Wow! There's so much more, but it is a very compelling read. I loved the way it was written, and I couldn't put the book down throughout the dramatic, climactic ending. I'd love to see the 1945 Joan Crawford movie. She'd be perfect for this one!</span>
