<span id="freeTextContainer1846668485291028249">Superb. A Noir in the time of noirs. Just dark and twisty enough. Fully saturated story. <br/><br/>Blood ties versus courage and truth. The family dynamics of child psychopathy. The ways and means of resilience. <br/><br/>Nothing shocked or overcame me, and I thoroughly enjoyed rooting for emerging-modern Mildred in all her human strength and frailty and the heavy bonds of fealty. </span>

